{
  "texts": [
    "As usual, the NSDCG is obtained as the NDCG, dividing the SDCG of the anonymized note by the SDCG of the ideal and original note, being expressed as a percentage value:",
    "In summary, six new metrics were proposed for a fair evaluation of clinical de-identification methods.",
    "ALID, LR, LRDI, and LRQI leverage the concept of LD and focus on anonymization sensitivity, i.e., assessing whether all sensitive entities have been masked.",
    "On the other hand, JSC and NSDCG measure the retention of clinical information.",
    "Table 1 provides a brief description of each metric."
  ]
}